Taita Taveta government staff running for election have until November 11 to make a formal declaration to the governor's office. According to an internal memo from Governor John Mruttu's office, this is to safeguard service delivery. It has come to my attention that some officers have intentions and ambitions to contest in the oncoming elections and I would like to affirm that it is every individual right and I wish them all the best in their endeavors, reads the memo.Mruttu states that his government is to serve the people and personal ambitions should not conflict with the constitutional duty to serve the residents. As the governor I'm under oath to serve the people and it's my situation to handle this emerging situation, he said.